DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Golden Chanterelle  Nov–Feb 2027
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Nov → Feb 2027\nPEAK:   Mar · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Can
 tharellus californicus\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Oak woodland\, m
 ixed forest\nRegions:    Marin · East · Peninsula · Santacruz\n\nCalifo
 rnia's state mushroom and the world's largest chanterelle. Golden-yellow w
 ith forking ridges. Rich apricot aroma when fresh.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Jack-
 o'-lantern mushroom (Omphalotus olivascens) is toxic. Grows in dense clust
 ers at tree base with true gills\, not ridges.\n\n💡 Tip: Peak after fir
 st heavy winter rains. Cut at base — never pull.\n\n— Cedar · Norther
 n California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
