SUMMARY:🍄 Pacific Golden Chanterelle  Nov–Feb 2027
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Nov → Feb 2027\nPEAK:   Mar · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Can
 tharellus formosus\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Douglas-fir and tano
 ak forest\nRegions:    Marin · Santacruz\n\nFound under Douglas-fir and t
 anoak in northern coastal forests. Similar excellent flavor to golden chan
 terelle.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Jack-o'-lantern mushroom. Check for forking rid
 ges\, not true gills.\n\n💡 Tip: More common at higher elevations and Ma
 rin.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
