DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261202
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Yellowfoot Chanterelle  Dec–Mar 2027
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Dec → Mar 2027\nPEAK:   Apr · Nov\n\nSpecies:    Cra
 terellus tubaeformis\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Mossy conifer duff\, D
 ouglas-fir forest\nRegions:    Marin · Santacruz\n\nSmall funnel-shaped c
 hanterelle with hollow bright yellow stem. Grows in troops in wet mossy co
 nifer forest.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No serious lookalikes. Yellow hollow stem 
 is distinctive.\n\n💡 Tip: Excellent dried — flavor intensifies. Look 
 in very wet mossy spots.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
