DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Oyster Mushroom  Nov–Mar 2027
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Nov → Mar 2027\nPEAK:   Apr · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Ple
 urotus ostreatus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Dead hardwood logs and stu
 mps\nRegions:    Marin · East · Peninsula · Santacruz\n\nFan-shaped clu
 sters on dead alder\, cottonwood\, and oak. Decurrent white gills\, mild s
 avory flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Angel wings (Pleurocybella porrigens) — 
 small\, white\, on conifers only.\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest young before edges 
 curl. Best sautéed in butter at high heat.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Calif
 ornia Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
