SUMMARY:🍄 Candy Cap  Jan–Mar
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jan → Mar\nPEAK:   Apr · Dec\n\nSpecies:    Lactariu
 s rubidus\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Oak and tanoak woodland\nRegi
 ons:    Marin · East · Santacruz\n\nSmall reddish-brown mushroom. Dried 
 specimens have a powerful maple syrup aroma used in desserts.\n\n⚠ Looka
 like: Other small brown Lactarius species. Dried candy cap smells powerful
 ly of maple syrup — others do not.\n\n💡 Tip: Aroma only develops when
  dried. Peak January–February.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Forag
 ing
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
