SUMMARY:🍄 Black Trumpet  Dec–Feb 2027
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Dec → Feb 2027\nPEAK:   Mar · Nov\n\nSpecies:    Cra
 terellus cornucopioides\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Oak woodland\, 
 often tanoak and live oak\nRegions:    Marin · East · Peninsula\n\nThin 
 funnel-shaped\, smoky gray to black. Extraordinarily earthy\, truffle-like
  flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes. Thin black funnel shap
 e is unique.\n\n💡 Tip: Look DOWN — nearly invisible against dark soil
 . Outstanding dried.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
