DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260302
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 King Bolete / Porcini  Mar–Apr
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Mar → Apr\nPEAK:   May · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Boletus 
 edulis\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Under pine and Douglas-fir\nRegi
 ons:    Marin · Santacruz\n\nThe prized king — brown cap\, white spongy
  pores\, meaty white flesh.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Satan's bolete (Rubroboletus
  satanas) — red pores\, blue staining. Never eat bolete with red pores.\
 n\n💡 Tip: Slice lengthwise to check for worms. Avoid any bolete with re
 d pores.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
