DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Nov → Dec\nPEAK:   Jan · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Tricholo
 ma murrillianum\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabitat:    Tanoak and madrone f
 orest\nRegions:    Marin · Santacruz\n\nHighly aromatic — spicy\, cinna
 mon-like scent. Often buried in duff. Prized in Japanese cuisine.\n\n⚠ L
 ookalike: Smith's amanita (Amanita smithiana) — toxic. Check for spicy c
 innamon smell.\n\n💡 Tip: Distinctive spicy aroma is the key ID feature.
 \n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
