DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌊 California Kombu  Jun–Jul
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jun → Jul\nPEAK:   May · Aug\n\nSpecies:    Laminari
 a setchellii\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Intertidal rock pools\, ex
 posed subtidal zone\nRegions:    Sonoma · Mendocino\n\nHarvested commerci
 ally along the Sonoma Coast since the 1990s by Strong Arm Farm. Thick leat
 hery blades used in broths and dashi. Highest natural glutamate content of
  any local seaweed — deep umami flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous l
 ookalikes — large flat brown kelp blades on rocks.\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest 
 June–July at low tide only. Cut blade leaving holdfast intact so it regr
 ows annually. Do not rinse off white powdery surface — it's glutamates.\
 n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
