SUMMARY:🌊 Wakame (Alaria)  May–Jul
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jul\nPEAK:   Apr · Aug\n\nSpecies:    Alaria m
 arginata\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Rocky intertidal\, exposed to 
 wave action\nRegions:    Sonoma · Mendocino · Marin\n\nRibbon-like brown
  seaweed related to Japanese wakame. Subtly sweet\, tender after blanching
 . Excellent in miso soup and seaweed salads.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerou
 s lookalikes — distinctive midrib running down center of blade.\n\n💡 
 Tip: Harvest before July when blades become tattered. Leave the holdfast a
 nd 4 inches of stipe to allow regrowth.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Californi
 a Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
