SUMMARY:🌊 Bladderwrack  May–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Aug\nPEAK:   Apr · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Fucus di
 stichus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Mid-intertidal rocky shores\nRegion
 s:    Sonoma · Mendocino · Marin · Peninsula\n\nOlive-green branching s
 eaweed with paired air bladders. Rich in iodine\, fucoidan\, and antioxida
 nts. Primarily medicinal — broth and tea use. Found from the Sonoma Coas
 t throughout the Bay Area.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — d
 istinctive branching pattern with air bladders.\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest only 
 the tips. Excellent for stocks and medicinal teas. High iodine — use in 
 small amounts.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
