SUMMARY:🌊 Turkish Towel Seaweed  May–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Aug\nPEAK:   Apr · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Mastocar
 pus papillatus\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Mid to low intertidal\, 
 rocky coasts\nRegions:    Sonoma · Mendocino · Marin\n\nThick dark red s
 eaweed named for its rough textured surface. Used as a natural thickener (
 contains carrageenan). Excellent in broths and as a umami-adding ingredien
 t.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — distinctive dark red\, bu
 mpy textured fronds.\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest small amounts. Rinse thoroughly.
  Simmer in water — releases carrageenan to thicken stocks naturally.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
