SUMMARY:🌊 Feather Boa Kelp  Jun–Sep
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jun → Sep\nPEAK:   May · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Egregia 
 menziesii\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Rocky intertidal and subtidal zon
 es\nRegions:    Sonoma · Mendocino · Marin\n\nSpectacular kelp reaching 
 30 feet. Air bladders make distinctive snapping pickles. Found washed on b
 eaches after winter swells — no diving needed.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dang
 erous lookalikes — long strap-like fronds with feathery side blades and 
 small air floats.\n\n💡 Tip: Collect fresh cast specimens from beach —
  no harvesting of live attached plants needed. The small air balloons pick
 le beautifully.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
