SUMMARY:🌊 Periwinkle  Jan–Dec
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jan → Dec\n\nSpecies:    Littorina scutulata\nDifficu
 lty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Rocky intertidal zones above mussel beds\nRegio
 ns:    Sonoma · Mendocino · Marin · Peninsula\n\nSmall edible shore sna
 ils found clinging to rocks above the waterline. Traditional food on the S
 onoma and Mendocino coasts. Mild flavor\, chewy texture — like small cla
 ms.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes among edible snails at this 
 size.\n\n💡 Tip: Requires CA fishing license. Boil 3–4 minutes. Extrac
 t with a pin. Check for biotoxin advisories like mussels.\n\n— Cedar · 
 Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
