SUMMARY:🌊 Nori (Porphyra)  May–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Aug\nPEAK:   Apr · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Pyropia 
 perforata\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    High intertidal rock faces\nR
 egions:    Mendocino · Sonoma · Marin\n\nThe original wild nori. Thin pu
 rple-black sheets that dry into crispy snacks. Rich in protein\, B12\, and
  iron. Harvested commercially along the Mendocino and Sonoma coasts.\n\n
 ⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — thin translucent purple-black s
 heets on rocks.\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest June–July on low tides. Dry flat on
  screens in the sun. Can be eaten fresh\, dried\, or lightly toasted. Don'
 t harvest near outfalls.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
