SUMMARY:🌊 Dulse  May–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Aug\nPEAK:   Apr · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Palmaria
  mollis\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Low intertidal shaded rocky are
 as\nRegions:    Mendocino · Sonoma\n\nFan-shaped red seaweed with a disti
 nctively smoky\, salty\, bacon-like flavor when pan-fried dried. More comm
 on Mendocino north than Bay Area. Exceptionally nutritious.\n\n⚠ Lookali
 ke: No dangerous lookalikes — hand-shaped red fronds in sheltered low-ti
 de areas.\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest small amounts leaving frond base. Dried dul
 se fried in a dry pan until crispy tastes remarkably like bacon.\n\n— Ce
 dar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:COASTAL
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
