SUMMARY:🍇 Wood Strawberry  May–Jul
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jul\nPEAK:   Apr · Aug\n\nSpecies:    Fragaria
  vesca\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Open forest edges\, disturbed cleari
 ngs\, roadsides\nRegions:    Mendocino · Sonoma · Marin · Santacruz · 
 Foothills\n\nWild woodland strawberry intensely flavored and sweet — gro
 ws abundantly in Mendocino clearcuts and forest roads. Tiny fruit with ext
 raordinary flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — classic s
 trawberry leaves and fruit.\n\n💡 Tip: Forest roads after logging activi
 ty are prime spots — clearings create the sun exposure they need. Pick o
 nly ripe red berries.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:BERRIES
