SUMMARY:🌿 Cow Parsnip  Mar–May
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Mar → May\nPEAK:   Feb · Jun\n\nSpecies:    Heracleu
 m maximum\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabitat:    Moist coastal meadows\, st
 ream banks\, redwood forest edges\nRegions:    Mendocino · Sonoma · Mari
 n\n\nHuge native plant with edible young shoots and leaf stalks in very ea
 rly spring. The raw sap causes severe phototoxic burns on skin in sunlight
 . Traditional coastal food for Pomo and other tribes.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: DE
 ADLY lookalike: Poison hemlock (Conium maculatum) and water hemlock (Cicut
 a douglasii). Expert ID essential before ANY harvest.\n\n💡 Tip: EXPERT 
 ID REQUIRED. Harvest only young tightly-coiled shoots before unfolding. We
 ar gloves and long sleeves — sap causes blistering. Peel before eating. 
 Cook thoroughly.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
