SUMMARY:🌿 Redwood Sorrel  Mar–Jun
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Mar → Jun\nPEAK:   Feb · Jul\n\nSpecies:    Oxalis o
 regana\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Dense redwood forest floor\nRegions:
     Mendocino · Sonoma · Marin · Santacruz\n\nCarpet of clover-like lea
 ves on the redwood forest floor. Bright lemony flavor from oxalic acid. Th
 rives under the deepest redwood shade.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Cape sorrel (Oxal
 is pes-caprae) — also edible. Wood sorrel is shade-forest dwelling\, cap
 e sorrel is open disturbed areas.\n\n💡 Tip: Abundant in Mendocino and H
 umboldt redwood forests. Contains oxalates — enjoy as garnish not as mai
 n green. Flowers also edible.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
