SUMMARY:🍎 Wild Grape (Vitis californica)  Sep–Oct
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Sep → Oct\nPEAK:   Aug · Nov\n\nSpecies:    Vitis ca
 lifornica\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Stream sides\, canyon riparian co
 rridors\nRegions:    Napa · Sonoma · Marin · East · Peninsula · Lake\
 n\nNative California wild grape vines draped over streamside trees in Napa
  and Sonoma valleys. Small tart purple grapes excellent for juice\, jelly\
 , and wine. Young tendrils and leaves edible in spring.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: 
 No dangerous lookalikes — classic grape leaves\, tendrils\, and fruit.\n
 \n💡 Tip: Mark vines in spring when leaves emerge. Return in September w
 hen grapes are fully ripe. Grape leaves best picked small and tender.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:FRUITS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
