SUMMARY:🌿 California Mugwort  Apr–Jun
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Apr → Jun\nPEAK:   Mar · Jul\n\nSpecies:    Artemisi
 a douglasiana\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Stream banks\, disturbed 
 areas\, roadsides\nRegions:    Napa · Sonoma · Lake · East · Foothills
 \n\nAromatic native plant with silvery white-backed leaves. Strong sage-li
 ke flavor. Traditional Pomo and Miwok medicinal plant. Leaves used for fla
 voring\, stuffing\, and smudge. Young leaves edible in very small amounts.
 \n\n⚠ Lookalike: Other Artemisia species — all aromatic. Sage-like sme
 ll and fuzzy white-backed leaves are distinctive.\n\n💡 Tip: Used as fla
 voring herb — not eaten in quantity. Young spring leaves best. Strong fl
 avor — use sparingly like rosemary. Do not use during pregnancy.\n\n— 
 Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
