SUMMARY:🍎 Toyon (Christmas Berry)  Nov–Jan 2027
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Nov → Jan 2027\nPEAK:   Feb · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Het
 eromeles arbutifolia\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Chaparral\, oak wo
 odland\, coastal scrub\nRegions:    Napa · Sonoma · Marin · East · Pen
 insula · Santacruz · Lake · Foothills\n\nCalifornia holly — bright re
 d winter berries. Traditional Ohlone and Pomo food. Hollywood named for th
 is plant growing there abundantly.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalik
 es — iconic red berry clusters on native shrub.\n\n💡 Tip: Berries ast
 ringent raw — improve dramatically after frost or roasting/boiling. Trad
 itional preparation: roast or boil before eating.\n\n— Cedar · Northern
  California Foraging
CATEGORIES:FRUITS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
