SUMMARY:🌾 Wild Mustard (Sinapis)  Mar–May
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Mar → May\nPEAK:   Feb · Jun\n\nSpecies:    Sinapis 
 arvensis\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Vineyards\, roadsides\, disturbed 
 fields\nRegions:    Napa · Sonoma · Lake · East · Foothills\n\nThe mus
 tard blanketing Napa Valley vineyard floors in spring. Flowers\, young lea
 ves\, and seed pods all edible. Napa wine country is famous for its mustar
 d bloom.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — classic mustard sme
 ll confirms ID.\n\n💡 Tip: Young leaves before flowering are best — bl
 anch to reduce bitterness. Flowers excellent in salads. Seeds ground into 
 mustard sauce.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:INVASIVES
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
