RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Tule (Bulrush)  Apr–Jun
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Apr → Jun\nPEAK:   Mar · Jul\n\nSpecies:    Schoenop
 lectus acutus\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Clear Lake shoreline marshes\
 , freshwater margins\nRegions:    Lake · East · Napa\n\nThe iconic tule 
 of Clear Lake\, historically central to Pomo culture. Young shoots edible 
 raw or cooked in spring — peel the outer sheath to reveal a tender white
  core. Pollen edible like cattail pollen. Roots starchy.\n\n⚠ Lookalike:
  No dangerous lookalikes at Clear Lake — cylindrical stems without leave
 s are distinctive.\n\n💡 Tip: Clear Lake marshes have abundant tule. You
 ng spring shoots are the best eating — sweet and cucumber-like when peel
 ed. Harvest sustainably — tule habitat is critically important.\n\n— C
 edar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
