SUMMARY:🌿 Wapato (Arrowhead)  Sep–Nov
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Sep → Nov\nPEAK:   Aug · Dec\n\nSpecies:    Sagittar
 ia latifolia\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Shallow freshwater lake ma
 rgins\, Clear Lake edges\nRegions:    Lake · East\n\nAquatic plant with e
 dible starchy corms (root tubers) harvested in late summer and fall. Taste
 s like a mild potato. Important traditional food of many California tribes
  including Pomo at Clear Lake.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes 
 — distinctive arrowhead-shaped leaves.\n\n💡 Tip: Wade in shallow wate
 r in late summer — push roots loose with your feet and they float up. Bo
 il or roast corms like potatoes.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Forag
 ing
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
