SUMMARY:🌰 Blue Oak Acorn  Oct–Nov
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Oct → Nov\nPEAK:   Sep · Dec\n\nSpecies:    Quercus 
 douglasii\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Dry oak woodland\, interior v
 alleys and foothills\nRegions:    Lake · Napa · Foothills · East\n\nBlu
 e oak dominates the dry interior foothills of Lake County\, Napa\, and the
  Sierra foothills. Acorns are sweeter and lower in tannins than coast live
  oak — less leaching required.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes
 .\n\n💡 Tip: Blue oak acorns are among the best tasting California acorn
 s — lower tannin means shorter leaching time. Often only 1–2 changes o
 f water needed.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:NUTS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
