SUMMARY:🌾 Peppergrass  Feb–May
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Feb → May\nPEAK:   Jan · Jun\n\nSpecies:    Lepidium
  nitidum\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Dry disturbed areas\, trails\, roa
 dsides\nRegions:    Lake · Napa · East · Foothills\n\nCommon invasive w
 ith intensely peppery seeds and edible young leaves. Tiny plant but extrem
 ely flavorful seed pods. Related to watercress and garden cress.\n\n⚠ Lo
 okalike: No dangerous lookalikes — peppery smell and flat round seed pod
 s are distinctive.\n\n💡 Tip: Seed pods ground or used whole add intense
  black-pepper-like heat to dishes. Young leaves edible raw. Very common on
  dry trails in Lake and Napa counties.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California
  Foraging
CATEGORIES:INVASIVES
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
