SUMMARY:🍎 Western Redbud (flowers)  Mar–Apr
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Mar → Apr\nPEAK:   Feb · May\n\nSpecies:    Cercis o
 ccidentalis\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Dry foothill slopes\, canyon wa
 lls\, chaparral edges\nRegions:    Foothills · Lake · Napa\n\nSpectacula
 r native tree covering Sierra foothill canyons in magenta in February-Marc
 h. Flower petals are edible — slightly sweet and sour. Young green seed 
 pods edible cooked like snap beans. Traditional Miwok and Nisenan food.\n\
 n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — brilliant magenta flowers on b
 are branches in early spring.\n\n💡 Tip: Eat the fresh flower petals raw
  as a garnish or in salads. Young flat green pods in April–May are best 
 cooked. Mark trees when blooming — return for pods.\n\n— Cedar · Nort
 hern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:FRUITS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
