DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260802
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌰 Gray Pine Nuts  Aug–Oct
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Aug → Oct\nPEAK:   Jul · Nov\n\nSpecies:    Pinus sa
 biniana\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Dry rocky foothill slopes\, oak
 -pine woodland\nRegions:    Foothills · Lake · Napa\n\nGray pine (digger
  pine) dominates the Sierra Nevada foothills. Large seeds in heavy cones 
 — some of the largest edible pine nuts in the world. Traditional staple 
 of foothill tribes.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — distinct
 ive gray-green sparse-needled pine with massive cones.\n\n💡 Tip: Cones 
 are very heavy (3–6 lbs) — approach carefully. Green cones harvested i
 n summer\, dried until scales open. Crack with a rock. Rich\, resinous fla
 vor distinct from Italian pine nuts.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California F
 oraging
CATEGORIES:NUTS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
