SUMMARY:🌿 Yampah  Jun–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jun → Aug\nPEAK:   May · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Perideri
 dia kelloggii\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabitat:    Open grassy slopes\, m
 eadow edges\, foothill grasslands\nRegions:    Foothills · Tahoe · Donne
 r\n\nSmall white-flowered carrot-family plant with sweet edible tuber root
 s. Traditional staple of Miwok\, Nisenan\, and Maidu people. Sweet\, carro
 t-like flavor raw or cooked. Often the most abundant traditional food plan
 t in Sierra meadows.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: DEADLY lookalike: Poison hemlock (C
 onium maculatum) and water hemlock (Cicuta douglasii) look nearly identica
 l. Carrot-family expert ID absolutely required.\n\n💡 Tip: EXPERT ID REQ
 UIRED — Do not harvest without confirmed ID from a specialist. Anise-lik
 e smell of crushed leaves and small clustered tubers are key features. Wat
 er hemlock is deadly and in same habitat.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Califor
 nia Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
