SUMMARY:🌿 Miner's Lettuce (foothill)  Feb–Apr
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Feb → Apr\nPEAK:   Jan · May\n\nSpecies:    Claytoni
 a perfoliata\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Moist shaded stream banks\, fo
 othill canyon bottoms\nRegions:    Foothills · Tahoe · Napa · Lake\n\nA
 ppears in large colonies along foothill stream banks and shaded canyon flo
 ors. Named by Gold Rush miners who ate it to prevent scurvy. Same species 
 as Bay Area miner's lettuce but often more abundant.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No 
 dangerous lookalikes — round lily-pad leaves with flower through center.
 \n\n💡 Tip: Look along shaded creek banks in foothill canyons in Februar
 y–April. Entire plant edible raw. Best before flowering.\n\n— Cedar ·
  Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
