SUMMARY:🍇 Sierra Gooseberry  Jul–Sep
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jul → Sep\nPEAK:   Jun · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Ribes ro
 ezlii\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Rocky slopes and ridges in mixed 
 conifer forest\nRegions:    Foothills · Tahoe · Donner\n\nNative goosebe
 rry of the Sierra Nevada with reddish-purple spiny berries. Intensely tart
  and flavorful. Important bear food. Traditional food of Miwok and Maidu p
 eoples.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — spiny gooseberry shr
 ub with hanging berries.\n\n💡 Tip: Wear gloves — shrub and sometimes 
 berries have spines. Tart raw — excellent in preserves. Bears compete 
 — check higher elevation shrubs first.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Californ
 ia Foraging
CATEGORIES:BERRIES
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
