SUMMARY:🌿 Mountain Misery (Chamaebatia)  May–Jun
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jun\nPEAK:   Apr · Jul\n\nSpecies:    Chamaeba
 tia foliolosa\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabitat:    Sierra Nevada mixed co
 nifer forest\, often with ponderosa pine\nRegions:    Foothills · Tahoe\n
 \nAromatic sticky ground cover smelling of pine and resin. Young leaves an
 d flowers used as a tea by Nisenan and Miwok peoples. Not widely known as 
 edible.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes in its distinctive stick
 y aromatic habitat.\n\n💡 Tip: Niche use only — sticky leaves steeped 
 as aromatic tea. Very small amounts — not a food plant per se\, more of 
 a traditional herbal beverage. Distinctive sweet-resinous aroma.\n\n— Ce
 dar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
