SUMMARY:🌿 Mariposa Lily (bulb)  May–Jul
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jul\nPEAK:   Apr · Aug\n\nSpecies:    Calochor
 tus venustus\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabitat:    Dry grassy slopes and o
 pen forest in the Sierra foothills\nRegions:    Foothills · Tahoe\n\nBeau
 tiful California native with a small edible starchy bulb. Traditional food
  of Miwok and other Sierra peoples. Nutty\, mild flavor raw or cooked. DO 
 NOT HARVEST from protected or sensitive areas.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No danger
 ous lookalikes but protected species — only harvest invasive-area popula
 tions with permission.\n\n💡 Tip: ONLY forage where population is abunda
 nt and on private land with permission. Bulb is small — dig carefully wi
 th a digging stick leaving soil undisturbed. Cook like a small potato.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
