SUMMARY:🍇 Sierra Currant  Jul–Sep
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jul → Sep\nPEAK:   Jun · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Ribes ne
 vadense\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Moist mountain slopes\, stream bank
 s\, conifer forest\nRegions:    Tahoe · Donner · Foothills\n\nBlue-purpl
 e mountain currant common throughout the Tahoe basin. Tart\, juicy berries
  excellent for jam\, syrup\, and fresh eating. Clusters of 5–15 berries 
 hanging below branches.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — clas
 sic currant appearance with smooth berries.\n\n💡 Tip: Found along strea
 m banks and in moist forest in the Tahoe basin at 5\,000–9\,000 ft eleva
 tion. Peak July–August. Less spiny than gooseberry.\n\n— Cedar · Nort
 hern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:BERRIES
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
