SUMMARY:🍇 Dwarf Bilberry  Aug–Sep
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Aug → Sep\nPEAK:   Jul · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Vacciniu
 m caespitosum\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Subalpine meadow edges\, rock
 y ridges\, moist slopes above 7\,000 ft\nRegions:    Tahoe · Donner\n\nLo
 w-growing blueberry relative of high Sierra and Tahoe. Small deep blue-bla
 ck berries with intense blueberry flavor. Found on rocky slopes and subalp
 ine meadow edges.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes at elevation 
 — only small blueberry-like shrub in this habitat.\n\n💡 Tip: Look on 
 rocky exposed ridges above 7\,000 ft elevation. Peak late July–August. B
 erries tiny but extremely flavorful — best eaten fresh trailside.\n\n—
  Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:BERRIES
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
