SUMMARY:🍄 Suillus Mushroom  Oct–Dec
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Oct → Dec\nPEAK:   Jan · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Suillus 
 pungens\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Under ponderosa and shore pine 
 exclusively\nRegions:    Tahoe · Donner · Foothills\n\nSlimy-capped bole
 te found exclusively under pines at Tahoe and throughout the Sierra. Large
  meaty caps with spongy pores. Cousin of porcini — good flavor when peel
 ed and cooked.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Other Suillus species — all edible but 
 variable quality. Avoid any bolete with red pores or that stains blue.\n\n
 💡 Tip: Always peel the slimy upper skin before cooking — it's less di
 gestible. Never eat if flesh stains blue when cut. Sauté at high heat to 
 cook off excess moisture.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
