SUMMARY:🌿 Fir Tips (spruce tips)  May–Jun
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jun\nPEAK:   Apr · Jul\n\nSpecies:    Abies ma
 gnifica\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Mixed conifer and red fir forest\, 
 6\,000–9\,000 ft elevation\nRegions:    Tahoe · Donner\n\nBrilliant lim
 e-green new growth tips of red fir in spring. Bright citrusy flavor from v
 itamin C. Used in syrups\, salt\, vinegar\, and tea. Popular among wild fo
 od chefs.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes among California firs.
 \n\n💡 Tip: Harvest only the soft bright-green new growth tips — they 
 snap off cleanly. Available just 2–3 weeks in May–June. Make into simp
 le syrup or infused salt.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
