DESCRIPTION:PEAK SEASON: Jul → Jul\nFULL SEASON: May · Jun\n\nSpecies:  
   Abies magnifica\nHabitat:    Mixed conifer and red fir forest\, 6\,000
 –9\,000 ft elevation\nRegions:    Tahoe · Donner\n\n💡 Tip: Harvest o
 nly the soft bright-green new growth tips — they snap off cleanly. Avail
 able just 2–3 weeks in May–June. Make into simple syrup or infused sal
 t.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS,PEAK
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
