UID:cedar-s-0351@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Labrador Tea  Jun–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jun → Aug\nPEAK:   May · Sep\n\nSpecies:    Rhododen
 dron columbianum\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Subalpine bogs\, wet m
 eadow edges\, stream margins above 6\,000 ft\nRegions:    Tahoe · Donner\
 n\nAromatic shrub of subalpine bogs and wet meadows. Dried leaves steeped 
 as a traditional tea used by indigenous people across the Sierra. Mild\, s
 lightly resinous\, pleasant flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Bog Labrador tea is 
 distinctive — fuzzy orange-brown undersides on leaves. Do not confuse wi
 th toxic Ledum species — use established ID guides.\n\n💡 Tip: Use sma
 ll amounts for tea — large amounts can cause headaches. Dried leaves pre
 ferred over fresh. Found at the margins of high-elevation wet meadows.\n\n
 — Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
