DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍇 Western Serviceberry  Jul–Sep
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jul → Sep\nPEAK:   Jun · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Amelanch
 ier alnifolia\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Rocky stream banks\, open for
 est edges\, canyon walls\nRegions:    Donner · Tahoe · Foothills\n\nServ
 iceberry (also called Juneberry or Saskatoon) — one of the most importan
 t traditional foods in the Sierra Nevada. Sweet\, mild berries resembling 
 blueberries. Eaten fresh\, dried into pemmican\, or made into jam.\n\n⚠ 
 Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — white-petaled spring flowers and bl
 ueberry-like summer berries.\n\n💡 Tip: One of the most underrated wild 
 berries. Ripe berries are deep purple-blue and sweet. Found along rocky st
 ream banks in Donner Pass and Truckee areas.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Cali
 fornia Foraging
CATEGORIES:BERRIES
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
