DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Mountain Sorrel  Jul–Sep
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jul → Sep\nPEAK:   Jun · Oct\n\nSpecies:    Oxyria d
 igyna\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Rocky alpine and subalpine slopes\, t
 alus fields above 8\,000 ft\nRegions:    Donner · Tahoe\n\nAlpine plant o
 f rocky high-elevation slopes. Kidney-shaped leaves with intensely sour le
 mony flavor from oxalic acid. Traditional food of many Sierra tribes eaten
  raw.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes — kidney-shaped leaves w
 ith bright lemony taste at elevation.\n\n💡 Tip: High in oxalates — ea
 t small amounts as a trail condiment\, not a main green. Excellent added t
 o trailside water for flavor.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
