DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🍄 Sierra Nevada Porcini  Jun–Aug
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: Jun → Aug\nPEAK:   May · Sep · Dec\n\nSpecies:    B
 oletus edulis\nDifficulty: Moderate\nHabitat:    Under pine\, fir\, and sp
 ruce in mixed Sierra conifer forest\nRegions:    Donner · Tahoe · Foothi
 lls\n\nKing bolete fruits in the Sierra Nevada in spring after snowmelt (M
 ay–July under pines) and again in fall (September–October). Tahoe and 
 Donner area are prime locations — one of the best mushroom regions in No
 rth America.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: Satan's bolete (Rubroboletus satanas) — r
 ed pores\, blue staining flesh. Never eat any bolete with red pores.\n\n
 💡 Tip: Spring flush under melting snowbanks is the classic Sierra find.
  Slice lengthwise to check for worms before keeping.\n\n— Cedar · North
 ern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:MUSHROOMS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
