DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 Stinging Nettle (Sierra)  May–Jul
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jul\nPEAK:   Apr · Aug\n\nSpecies:    Urtica d
 ioica\nDifficulty: Easy\nHabitat:    Moist stream banks\, disturbed mounta
 in meadows\nRegions:    Donner · Tahoe · Foothills · Mendocino · Sonom
 a\n\nStinging nettle grows abundantly along Sierra Nevada stream banks and
  in moist meadows. Spring emergence is a few weeks later than coastal popu
 lations at same calendar date.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous lookalikes 
 — sting confirms identity immediately.\n\n💡 Tip: Wear gloves. Harvest
  young tops only at 4–6 inches tall. Sting neutralized by blanching 1 mi
 nute or cooking. Rich in iron and protein.\n\n— Cedar · Northern Califo
 rnia Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
