BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cedar-s-0368@cedar.norCal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY
SUMMARY:🌿 White Fir Cambium  May–Jun
DESCRIPTION:SEASON: May → Jun\nPEAK:   Apr · Jul\n\nSpecies:    Abies co
 ncolor\nDifficulty: Hard/Expert\nHabitat:    Mixed conifer forest througho
 ut Sierra Nevada\nRegions:    Donner · Tahoe · Foothills\n\nThe inner ba
 rk (cambium) of white fir is edible and was eaten by Maidu and Washoe peop
 les as a spring food. Scraped from fallen or recently felled trees only. S
 tarchy\, slightly sweet\, piney flavor.\n\n⚠ Lookalike: No dangerous loo
 kalikes among California white firs.\n\n💡 Tip: ONLY harvest from fallen
  or dead trees — never damage living trees. Scrape inner bark layer (gre
 en side of bark). Cook or dry and grind into flour. A survival food\, not 
 a daily staple.\n\n— Cedar · Northern California Foraging
CATEGORIES:GREENS
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
